<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Holotype (Fig. 17A) is a blackish brown fragment of 3.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×3×">x3x</normalizedToken>
1 cm (live colour also noted as black). Surface lumpy but smooth, shiny. Consistency firm, compressible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Skeleton: at the surface a crust of microscleres, overlying a dense confused mass of calthrops.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Spicules: calthrops, sanidasters, compressed sanidasters (pseudasters).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Calthrops of holotype (Fig. 17B) equiangled, regular, 105
<normalizedToken originalValue="–170.8–">-170.8-</normalizedToken>
223 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
14
<normalizedToken originalValue="–20.7–">-20.7-</normalizedToken>
28 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(cladomes 182
<normalizedToken originalValue="–286.3–">-286.3-</normalizedToken>
365 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
); of the paratype (Fig. 18A), equiangled, some with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘hooked’">'hooked'</normalizedToken>
apices, 33
<normalizedToken originalValue="–177.2–">-177.2-</normalizedToken>
252 
